  "summary": "Mutsu and the narrator arrive at the office of Professor Nakatani, a renowned neuroscientist, at National K University Hospital. Mutsu requests strict confidentiality before entering the room, leaving the narrator to wait in the hallway for thirty minutes. When Mutsu emerges, he indicates the meeting was successful but remains secretive about the details. The two men return to Kyoto City after nine o'clock.\n\nThe narrator visits Ophelia, who is in a weakened state and speaks cryptically, suggesting that everything will crumble the following day. Afterward, the narrator encounters Mr. Sugiyama, also known as Kanai, who appears unsteady and potentially intoxicated. Kanai entrusts the narrator with a \"mist drawing\" and expresses a desire to protect someone, noting that Mukae believes the case will be resolved the next day.\n\nLater, a talkative individual named Kaname discusses a pattern regarding the Mirai family, observing that women who enter the family tend to die young. Kaname suggests this is not a mere coincidence but a structural issue within the family. He mentions that while his grandmother, Lady Hinata, lived a long life and broke this superstition, he suspects that Setsuko was brought into the family as a foster daughter to serve as a substitute to appease this perceived fate.",
